cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper studies epidemic processes taking place in temporal and adaptive networks, which are a type of social network. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm to tune the parameters describing the endogenous preventive measures. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the dynamics of epidemic processes and proposes a method to contain epidemics over time. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper uses numerical simulations to confirm the theoretical results. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also a possible category as the paper models the behavior of individuals in response to the state of the infection, which can be seen as a type of multiagent system.
